# text = To the feminine mind in some of its moods, all things that might be receive a temporary charm from comparison with what is; and since Adam did not want to marry Dinah himself, Lisbeth felt rather peevish on that score—as peevish as she would have been if he _had_ wanted to marry her, and so shut himself out from Mary Burge and the partnership as effectually as by marrying Hetty.
